"n.严厉谴责；束缚 【英】 n.严厉谴责(an adverse criticism)；束缚(restrictions) 【记】 来自strit(严格的)＋ ure 【例】 strictures against bribetaking(对受贿 行为的抨击)／moral strictures(道德束缚) n. 责难 = censure 【记】源于: strict(adj 严格的; 严厉的) 【反】eulogy(n 赞词) 【记】strict 严厉 stricture (n.)  c.1400, ""abnormal narrowing in a body part,"" from Late Latin strictura ""contraction, constriction,"" from past participle stem of stringere (2) ""to bind or draw tight"" (see strain (v.)). Sense of ""criticism, critical remark"" is first recorded 1650s, perhaps from the other Latin word stringere ""to touch lightly"" (see strigil)."
